# FinHub Financial Dashboard - Environment Variables Example
# 
# IMPORTANT: Copy this file to .env.local and add your actual API keys
# Never commit .env.local to version control!
#
# Required API Keys:

# Financial Modeling Prep API
# Get your free API key at: https://financialmodelingprep.com/developer/docs
# Required for: Stock data, financial statements, company profiles
NEXT_PUBLIC_FMP_API_KEY=your-fmp-api-key-here
FMP_API_KEY=your-fmp-api-key-here

# Perplexity AI API (Optional but recommended)
# Get your API key at: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
# Required for: AI-powered financial analysis in the chat feature
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=your-perplexity-api-key-here

# Supabase Configuration (Optional)
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard: Settings â†’ API
# Required for: Authentication, data persistence features
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here

# Security Notes:
# - NEVER commit .env.local to Git
# - Regenerate any API keys that may have been exposed
# - Use environment variables in your hosting platform for production